Hi,

You seem to be confusing ?Github? with Bioconductor?s private git repository. Please note that, git.bioconductor.org<http://git.bioconductor.org> is a Bioconductor hosted privately administered git server. Github, is hosted by the company Github.com<http://Github.com>.

Developers of Bioconductor are supported only for git.bioconductor.org<http://git.bioconductor.org>. I suggest you read, http://bioconductor.org/developers/how-to/git/. You are trying to access Github using Bioconductor?s git application. This is not a service we provide.

Best,

Nitesh

